7
00:01:13,707 --> 00:01:18,775
♪

8
00:01:18,808 --> 00:01:33,743
♪

9
00:01:33,743 --> 00:01:36,545
♪

10
00:01:38,711 --> 00:01:46,113
♪

11
00:01:50,013 --> 00:01:56,848
<i>[birds chirping]</i>

12
00:01:56,881 --> 00:02:00,249
{\an1}Man... Elder Brother
sure has changed...

13
00:02:00,282 --> 00:02:04,149
{\an1}He's just so strict!  I feel
like he's going to alienate
everyone else...

14
00:02:04,182 --> 00:02:07,883
{\an1}Oh!  There you are! I've been
looking for you, Ashura!

15
00:02:07,916 --> 00:02:09,484
Taizo!

16
00:02:09,517 --> 00:02:11,517
Have you finished with
your training for today?

17
00:02:11,550 --> 00:02:17,650
{\an4}Well, y'know, since Elder
Brother'll take over Ninshu, it
doesn't matter if I slack off a
bit...

18
00:02:17,684 --> 00:02:19,586
{\an1}...Or, you know, a lot.

19
00:02:19,618 --> 00:02:21,885
I see... [groan]

20
00:02:21,918 --> 00:02:23,919
{\an1}Well, it's less pressure on me!

21
00:02:23,953 --> 00:02:25,553
So, what's up?

22
00:02:25,587 --> 00:02:29,286
{\an1}Oh, uh, well, to tell you
the truth, I need a favor.

23
00:02:29,320 --> 00:02:30,887
Huh?

24
00:02:34,187 --> 00:02:38,522
<i>(Taizo)</i>
<i>Can you use Ninshu to knock down</i>
<i>a few of the trees around here?</i>

25
00:02:38,555 --> 00:02:40,888
{\an1}Huh? For what purpose?

26
00:02:40,921 --> 00:02:47,256
{\an4}Oh! Well, you see, if you were
able to clear a path through
this stretch of woods, we'd have
a shortcut to get to the fields.

27
00:02:47,289 --> 00:02:51,591
{\an1}It'd be easier on my mom. And
it's no big deal for you, right?

28
00:02:51,623 --> 00:02:54,492
{\an1}Oh, is that all? Just
leave it to me, then!

29
00:02:58,258 --> 00:03:02,392
<i>[bark cracking]</i>

30
00:03:04,859 --> 00:03:06,893
<i>[crash]</i>

31
00:03:08,527 --> 00:03:12,927
<i>[bark cracking]</i>

32
00:03:12,961 --> 00:03:15,328
<i>[crash]</i>

33
00:03:18,261 --> 00:03:20,962
<i>[bark cracking]</i>

34
00:03:20,995 --> 00:03:22,728
<i>[crash]</i>

35
00:03:25,296 --> 00:03:26,896
Will this do?

36
00:03:26,929 --> 00:03:29,396
Yeah! Thanks for
your help, buddy.

37
00:03:29,430 --> 00:03:32,997
{\an1}It wasn't a problem at all!
This kind of thing is easy.

38
00:03:39,565 --> 00:03:41,031
{\an1}<i>[painful breaths]</i>

39
00:03:41,065 --> 00:03:42,499
Taizo!

40
00:03:43,098 --> 00:03:46,699
{\an1}Elder Brother!  What's the
meaning of this?

41
00:03:48,399 --> 00:03:49,933
[gasp]

42
00:03:49,967 --> 00:03:52,967
{\an1}This man has committed
a serious crime.

43
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:56,968
{\an1}He fell some trees, and
sold them for profit.

44
00:03:57,001 --> 00:04:01,201
{\an1}Whatever is in this village
belongs to everyone who lives
here.  That's the law.

45
00:04:01,235 --> 00:04:05,236
{\an1}And you're just as guilty
as he is, Ashura.

46
00:04:05,269 --> 00:04:06,668
{\an1}Huh? I am, too?

47
00:04:06,702 --> 00:04:09,337
Yes, because you
were too gullible.

48
00:04:09,370 --> 00:04:13,904
{\an1}You allowed this man to deceive
you, and in doing so, you became
an accomplice to his crime.

49
00:04:13,937 --> 00:04:16,971
{\an1}Was needing a path
cleared just a lie?

50
00:04:17,004 --> 00:04:22,305
{\an1}My mom was really sick, and she
needed to get some medicine
quickly.

51
00:04:22,339 --> 00:04:25,906
{\an1}I'm sorry about this, Ashura.
I shouldn't have gotten you
involved.

52
00:04:25,939 --> 00:04:29,873
{\an1}Why didn't you just tell me the
truth?  I could've used Ninshu.

53
00:04:29,906 --> 00:04:32,307
{\an1}Yeah, I know, but my
Mom hates Ninshu.

54
00:04:32,341 --> 00:04:35,074
{\an1}She says that this
world doesn't need it.

55
00:04:35,107 --> 00:04:40,342
{\an1}Unfortunately, whether you
believe in Ninshu or not, a law
is still a law.

56
00:04:40,375 --> 00:04:47,009
{\an1}Now, You didn't know about this.
So just this one time, you will
be forgiven, Ashura.

57
00:04:47,042 --> 00:04:52,010
{\an1}Listen, Indra, perhaps you are
taking all of this too far.

58
00:04:52,043 --> 00:04:54,776
{\an1}Everyone makes mistakes
every now and again.

59
00:04:54,810 --> 00:04:58,644
{\an1}Passing judgment on them demands
that you exercise prudence.

60
00:04:58,677 --> 00:05:00,711
{\an1}Yes, I know that, Father.

61
00:05:00,744 --> 00:05:06,112
{\an1}At the same time, when a crime's
committed, proper punishment
must be carried out...

62
00:05:06,146 --> 00:05:09,580
{\an1}...since only then will it act
to deter future crimes.

63
00:05:09,614 --> 00:05:11,180
{\an1}Brother...

64
00:05:22,115 --> 00:05:26,582
[groan]

65
00:05:26,616 --> 00:05:28,416
Ashura!

66
00:05:28,450 --> 00:05:29,782
{\an1}Shh Let me get you out.

67
00:05:29,816 --> 00:05:30,816
But--!

68
00:05:30,849 --> 00:05:36,618
{\an1}It's okay. I'll take full
responsibility for this.

69
00:05:41,651 --> 00:05:43,051
[gasp]

70
00:05:44,751 --> 00:05:46,086
Elder Brother--!

71
00:05:46,119 --> 00:05:49,952
{\an1}Well, Ashura... just what do you
think you're doing with that
man?

72
00:05:49,986 --> 00:05:52,187
{\an1}Please just look the other way!

73
00:05:52,220 --> 00:05:54,587
{\an1}He didn't do what he did
with malicious intent.

74
00:05:54,621 --> 00:05:57,687
{\an1}But the law is still the law.

75
00:05:57,721 --> 00:06:00,522
{\an1}Haven't you already made an
example out of him?

76
00:06:00,555 --> 00:06:04,456
{\an1}That isn't something you
get to decide, Ashura.

77
00:06:04,489 --> 00:06:07,722
{\an1}Listen, I'll convince
my brother somehow.

78
00:06:07,755 --> 00:06:09,556
{\an1}You just go.
Get outta here.

79
00:06:09,590 --> 00:06:11,723
Thanks, Ashura!
I owe you one.

80
00:06:12,856 --> 00:06:16,158
{\an1}Well then, if you're going to
break the law...

81
00:06:16,191 --> 00:06:17,224
[grunt]

82
00:06:17,258 --> 00:06:20,291
{\an1}...then you can take the
punishment instead of him.

83
00:06:21,057 --> 00:06:23,459
[grunt]

84
00:06:23,492 --> 00:06:25,125
{\an1}Stop this, Elder Brother!

85
00:06:26,292 --> 00:06:28,692
[grunt]

86
00:06:30,393 --> 00:06:33,826
{\an1}Ashura, why do we have a
system of laws in place?

87
00:06:33,859 --> 00:06:37,027
{\an1}What's the purpose of the
power Ninshu provides us?

88
00:06:37,060 --> 00:06:42,562
{\an4}If you can't answer such
questions yourself, then you
should just listen to me and
obey me.

89
00:06:42,595 --> 00:06:44,395
{\an1}Go calm yourself.

90
00:06:47,463 --> 00:06:50,296
Elder Brother...

91
00:07:03,331 --> 00:07:06,166
[gasp]

92
00:07:06,199 --> 00:07:07,865
Oh, Father!

93
00:07:10,099 --> 00:07:12,133
Today's the day
when Shiro died...

94
00:07:12,167 --> 00:07:16,834
{\an1}Back then, if Shiro and Elder
Brother weren't there,  I
would've died.

95
00:07:16,867 --> 00:07:19,700
{\an1}<i>I'm alive thanks to</i>
<i>their strength.</i>

96
00:07:19,734 --> 00:07:24,502
{\an1}[sigh] You know, you really do
possess a truly gentle heart.

97
00:07:24,536 --> 00:07:28,269
{\an1}The complete opposite
of Indra...

98
00:07:28,302 --> 00:07:30,537
{\an1}Well, Elder Brother's a genius.

99
00:07:30,570 --> 00:07:34,970
{\an1}He can do anything by himself,
and he has the power to do so.

100
00:07:35,004 --> 00:07:37,171
{\an1}That's precisely why.
Huh?

101
00:07:37,204 --> 00:07:41,539
{\an1}What do you think of the eyes
Indra possesses now?

102
00:07:41,572 --> 00:07:43,539
{\an1}What do I think about them?

103
00:07:43,572 --> 00:07:45,971
Well, I'm a bit
intimidated, I guess...

104
00:07:46,005 --> 00:07:51,339
{\an8}<i>(Thinking)</i>
<i>As I thought, Indra's Visual</i>
<i>Prowess wouldn't work with</i>
<i>Ashura.</i>

105
00:07:51,373 --> 00:07:54,040
{\an1}Something the matter, father?

106
00:07:54,073 --> 00:07:59,073
{\an1}There is something ominous about
Indra's eyes that even I cannot
fathom.

107
00:07:59,107 --> 00:08:05,408
{\an1}Looking into his eyes reminds
me... of my mother's eyes.

108
00:08:05,442 --> 00:08:10,643
{\an4}Maybe the answer is something
simple, like that Elder Brother
can see things that other
people just can't see...

109
00:08:10,675 --> 00:08:13,443
{\an1}And what exactly would that be?

110
00:08:13,477 --> 00:08:16,443
{\an1}Well, it could be
something really
advanced.

111
00:08:16,477 --> 00:08:19,677
{\an1}Like the ideal version of
Ninshu or the future.

112
00:08:19,710 --> 00:08:22,844
{\an1}I don't know for sure since I
don't possess the Sharingan.

113
00:08:22,877 --> 00:08:28,711
{\an1}But all those years ago, when
he and Shiro saved me, Elder
Brother was very kind.

114
00:08:28,745 --> 00:08:33,712
{\an1}And I still maintain faith that
Elder Brother's heart hasn't
changed since then.

115
00:08:33,746 --> 00:08:38,914
{\an1}I'll train harder and do my best
to become someone that Elder
Brother can rely on.

116
00:08:38,947 --> 00:08:47,148
{\an5}<i>(Hagoromo)</i>
<i>At that moment, I felt that I</i>
<i>understood for the first time,</i>
<i>why heaven had blessed me with</i>

117
00:08:47,182 --> 00:08:50,815
{\an1}<i>two sons... But then...</i>

118
00:08:52,049 --> 00:08:55,050
{\an1}<i>(Villager)</i>
<i>Hey, did you hear?</i>

119
00:08:55,083 --> 00:08:59,150
{\an5}<i>(Villager)</i>
<i>Yeah! Seems Lord Hagoromo is</i>
<i>finally going to name his</i>
<i>successor.</i>

120
00:08:59,184 --> 00:09:01,118
{\an1}Master Indra or
Master Ashura, huh?

121
00:09:01,151 --> 00:09:03,652
{\an1}I wonder which of them
it's going to be...

122
00:09:03,684 --> 00:09:09,519
{\an4}There's no doubt!  It just has
to be the elder one, Master
Indra, since he excels at
Ninshu!

123
00:09:11,152 --> 00:09:13,853
{\an1}And now, I'm going to
pick my successor.

124
00:09:23,787 --> 00:09:26,821
{\an1}I don't get it. What
is this, Father?

125
00:09:27,189 --> 00:09:31,523
{\an1}After the battle in which I
sealed away my mother, I
scattered the Ten Tails' parts,

126
00:09:31,557 --> 00:09:33,923
{\an1}which hold powers
unknown to man.

127
00:09:33,956 --> 00:09:39,124
{\an1}My followers and I repaired most
of the damage the battle caused.

128
00:09:39,157 --> 00:09:44,559
{\an1}But as it says in those scrolls,
there are still two regions that
remain damaged.

129
00:09:44,592 --> 00:09:50,493
{\an4}<i>Indra, Ashura. You are to go to</i>
<i>those lands and fix whatever</i>
<i>problems may have occurred</i>
<i>there.</i>

130
00:09:50,526 --> 00:09:56,394
{\an1}After I see your results, I'll
decide whom I'll entrust
Ninshu to.

131
00:09:56,427 --> 00:09:57,793
[gasps]

132
00:09:57,826 --> 00:09:59,693
Lord Hagoromo!

133
00:09:59,726 --> 00:10:02,562
Why, Father? Why
are you doing this?

134
00:10:02,595 --> 00:10:05,994
{\an1}I simply don't have enough
skill to inherit Ninshu!

135
00:10:06,028 --> 00:10:09,929
{\an1}In fact, I don't have any
desire to inherit it!

136
00:10:09,962 --> 00:10:12,095
{\an1}I'd be perfectly happy
helping Elder Brother.

137
00:10:12,129 --> 00:10:15,096
{\an1}That's for me to decide.

138
00:10:15,130 --> 00:10:18,729
{\an1}What will the two of you do when
you are out in the world, alone?

139
00:10:18,763 --> 00:10:22,498
{\an1}When I see that, everything
will fall into place.

140
00:10:29,499 --> 00:10:32,966
{\an1}Why do you think Father
chose to do this?

141
00:10:32,999 --> 00:10:37,300
{\an1}Don't worry.  I'm sure Father
will come to understand quickly.

142
00:10:37,333 --> 00:10:39,234
Yeah!

143
00:10:41,900 --> 00:10:45,468
{\an5}<i>(Gamamaru)</i>
<i>The younger one seems to have</i>
<i>matured into a kind and gentle</i>
<i>soul.</i>

144
00:10:45,502 --> 00:10:49,402
{\an1}But it's the older one who's
inherited the power of the
Sharingan, huh?

145
00:10:49,435 --> 00:10:57,170
{\an4}You know, it's possible... that
out of consideration for his
older brother, the younger one
might not return home.

146
00:10:57,204 --> 00:10:59,103
{\an1}I'll deal with that
if it happens.

147
00:10:59,137 --> 00:11:02,137
{\an1}What exactly is it that you're
looking to test with this?

148
00:11:02,170 --> 00:11:04,638
{\an1}It isn't a test of anything.

149
00:11:04,672 --> 00:11:08,772
{\an1}The eldest may excel, but
because of his power, he
has no faith in love.

150
00:11:08,805 --> 00:11:14,172
{\an1}The younger one doesn't have
the same kind of skill, but
he overflows with love.

151
00:11:14,206 --> 00:11:19,173
{\an1}I'm sure that Ninshu will come
to exert enormous influence in
this world.

152
00:11:19,207 --> 00:11:23,441
{\an1}And in order for Ninshu to take
the true and proper path...

153
00:11:23,474 --> 00:11:26,641
{\an1}...both power and love
will be necessary.

154
00:11:26,841 --> 00:11:31,075
{\an1}<i>I want my sons to grow during</i>
<i>their journeys.</i>

155
00:11:31,108 --> 00:11:35,943
{\an1}<i>...and, I hope, learn to nurture</i>
<i>Ninshu together.</i>

156
00:11:41,311 --> 00:11:44,010
{\an1}Hey! Enough already!
Just come out.

157
00:11:44,578 --> 00:11:46,711
{\an1}You knew I was here, huh?

158
00:11:46,744 --> 00:11:48,312
{\an1}Are you all right?

159
00:11:48,345 --> 00:11:51,479
{\an1}Yeah! As you can see...

160
00:11:51,513 --> 00:11:53,413
{\an1}Thanks for what you
did back then.

161
00:11:53,446 --> 00:11:56,112
{\an1}Don't mention it. So,
what is it? What's up?

162
00:11:56,146 --> 00:12:01,047
{\an1}After you helped me get free, I
hid out in a shack on a hill in
the backcountry.

163
00:12:01,080 --> 00:12:03,814
{\an1}Then Gasuka and Edashi.

164
00:12:03,847 --> 00:12:07,515
{\an1}I have big news! Ashura
is leaving on a journey!

165
00:12:07,548 --> 00:12:11,149
And that journey will
determine who the successor
of Ninshu will be.

166
00:12:11,182 --> 00:12:15,849
{\an4}Is what they said true?
Because, I mean, after I heard
that, I couldn't even sit still.

167
00:12:15,883 --> 00:12:18,016
{\an1}Listen, take me with you, okay?

168
00:12:18,050 --> 00:12:19,983
{\an1}Boy, I don't know about that.

169
00:12:20,016 --> 00:12:21,951
{\an1}Your mom's sick, isn't she?

170
00:12:21,984 --> 00:12:25,251
{\an1}Nah, she's okay now.  It seems
that the medicine really worked
well.

171
00:12:25,284 --> 00:12:26,784
{\an1}She's back to normal!

172
00:12:26,817 --> 00:12:30,652
{\an1}Besides, I told her about you,
and she said I should go and
help out.

173
00:12:30,686 --> 00:12:33,852
{\an1}But I thought that your mom
hated Ninshu!  So why--?

174
00:12:33,886 --> 00:12:36,119
{\an1}Aw, c'mon, those are
two separate things.

175
00:12:36,153 --> 00:12:39,386
{\an1}A man's obligation comes
before hating Ninshu.

176
00:12:39,420 --> 00:12:43,454
{\an1}You do realize that I'm
not gonna be coming home for
a long time, don't you?

177
00:12:43,487 --> 00:12:44,954
What? Seriously?

178
00:12:44,987 --> 00:12:49,155
{\an1}I'm certain that Elder Brother
will pass this test with
flying colors.

179
00:12:49,188 --> 00:12:54,389
{\an1}And if I don't return, then
Father will have no choice but
to pick him as his successor.

180
00:12:54,423 --> 00:12:57,056
{\an1}I see. That's so like you.

181
00:12:57,089 --> 00:12:59,557
{\an1}So then, where do
you intend to go?

182
00:12:59,591 --> 00:13:02,524
{\an1}Yeah, where should I go...?

183
00:13:02,557 --> 00:13:06,592
{\an1}Hey, didn't your dad say that
the people in the area where
you're supposed to go are having

184
00:13:06,625 --> 00:13:09,058
{\an1}a rough time or
something like that?

185
00:13:09,091 --> 00:13:10,992
{\an1}So wouldn't it be bad if
you didn't help them out?

186
00:13:11,025 --> 00:13:13,192
{\an1}Oh, yeah, I guess
that you're right...

187
00:13:13,226 --> 00:13:16,527
{\an1}I'd better go, and I'll figure
out the rest of it later.

188
00:13:16,560 --> 00:13:18,460
{\an1}All right!  Let's do it!

189
00:13:23,760 --> 00:13:34,229
{\an1}<i>[strong wind blowing]</i>

190
00:13:44,164 --> 00:13:47,764
Still, this place is
awfully far away!

191
00:13:51,265 --> 00:13:55,266
{\an1}[loud sigh]

192
00:13:55,299 --> 00:13:58,132
{\an1}According to the map, we should
be getting close by now, but...

193
00:14:04,534 --> 00:14:08,602
[groans]

194
00:14:09,901 --> 00:14:12,002
{\an1}We're in trouble! We're
all out of water!

195
00:14:12,035 --> 00:14:12,868
{\an1}Hey, don't worry.

196
00:14:12,902 --> 00:14:15,135
{\an1}What? How can I not
worry about it?

197
00:14:15,169 --> 00:14:17,336
{\an1}You can't do any Water
Jutsu, can you?

198
00:14:17,369 --> 00:14:20,036
{\an1}No, all I'm able to
do is Wind Jutsu.

199
00:14:20,070 --> 00:14:21,604
Well, then...

200
00:14:21,637 --> 00:14:24,104
{\an1}The Divine Tree; it's near.

201
00:14:24,137 --> 00:14:25,271
{\an3}Huh?

202
00:14:25,304 --> 00:14:27,737
{\an1}I'm able to sense
it with my chakra.

203
00:14:27,770 --> 00:14:34,639
{\an1}You know, a while ago, Father
told me that the Divine Tree
gave Ninshu Chakra its power.

204
00:14:39,240 --> 00:14:42,441
Hey--!

205
00:14:45,773 --> 00:14:49,808
{\an1}[panting breaths]
Well, looks like we made it.

206
00:14:54,042 --> 00:14:59,643
<i>[birds chirping]</i>

207
00:14:59,676 --> 00:15:04,444
{\an4}It's quite a surprise to find a
place as fertile as this right
in the middle of such a barren
area!

208
00:15:04,477 --> 00:15:09,545
{\an1}How could a village like this be
struggling like Lord Hagoromo
said?

209
00:15:09,578 --> 00:15:11,978
What's wrong?

210
00:15:12,011 --> 00:15:13,145
{\an1}We've been surrounded...

211
00:15:13,179 --> 00:15:14,246
[gasp]

212
00:15:17,012 --> 00:15:20,113
{\an1}And just who are you!?

213
00:15:20,146 --> 00:15:23,614
{\an1}We're nobody you need to worry
about.  We're merely travelers.

214
00:15:23,647 --> 00:15:26,681
{\an1}We've had a lot of robbers
targeting our village lately.

215
00:15:26,715 --> 00:15:29,214
{\an1}We're not robbers. Please
believe us.  We don't want
trouble!

216
00:15:29,248 --> 00:15:31,382
{\an1}Never mind, just get 'em!

217
00:15:31,415 --> 00:15:33,716
{\an1}Quick, Taizo, climb a tree!

218
00:15:34,482 --> 00:15:36,115
{\an1}[frightened cries]

219
00:15:36,148 --> 00:15:39,283
{\an1}Please, stop this! I have
no desire to fight you!

220
00:15:39,316 --> 00:15:41,483
{\an1}Well then get out of this
village right away!

221
00:15:43,050 --> 00:15:43,917
[gasp]

222
00:15:45,684 --> 00:15:46,984
{\an1}Hey, are you all right?!

223
00:15:47,551 --> 00:15:48,750
{\an1}Don't touch me!

224
00:15:48,783 --> 00:15:52,518
{\an1}It's okay! Hold still.
I'll heal you.

225
00:15:54,418 --> 00:15:57,152
I just hope this
actually works...

226
00:15:58,486 --> 00:16:01,153
{\an1}Amazing...

227
00:16:03,587 --> 00:16:05,687
{\an1}What's this ruckus about?

228
00:16:05,721 --> 00:16:07,921
{\an1}Oh!  Lord Elder...

229
00:16:14,955 --> 00:16:15,788
<i>(Taizo)</i>
<i>What a feast!</i>

230
00:16:15,822 --> 00:16:17,989
{\an1}And we can really
eat all of this?!

231
00:16:18,022 --> 00:16:20,490
{\an1}Please don't hesitate,
just eat up.

232
00:16:20,523 --> 00:16:23,423
{\an1}And I apologize for
the rudeness earlier.

233
00:16:23,457 --> 00:16:25,524
{\an1}Don't worry about it, really.

234
00:16:25,558 --> 00:16:30,691
{\an1}You know... it's quite a shock
to see such a fertile area.
This land's barren.

235
00:16:30,725 --> 00:16:33,592
{\an1}Well, this village
is very special.

236
00:16:33,626 --> 00:16:35,025
Special?

237
00:16:35,058 --> 00:16:40,993
{\an1}Anyway, there's not much to do
here, so please have a relaxing
stay.

238
00:16:52,061 --> 00:16:56,263
{\an1}[yawn] You're up early, Ashura.

239
00:16:56,296 --> 00:17:00,696
{\an1}This sure is a wonderful place,
isn't it? I mean, the food and
water taste great...

240
00:17:00,730 --> 00:17:04,763
{\an1}...and as luck would have it,
that girl you saved is quite
a beauty, too.

241
00:17:04,796 --> 00:17:07,364
{\an1}Nothing to worry about here.

242
00:17:07,397 --> 00:17:11,665
{\an1}Maybe you're right, but I can
still feel it, from over there.

243
00:17:11,698 --> 00:17:13,064
{\an1}Feel what?

244
00:17:13,098 --> 00:17:15,332
It's Chakra.

245
00:17:16,999 --> 00:17:18,865
Is that where the
Divine Tree is?

246
00:17:18,898 --> 00:17:22,333
Yeah, probably.

247
00:17:25,600 --> 00:17:28,368
{\an1}Hey, where are you going?

248
00:17:28,401 --> 00:17:31,101
I'd just like to
go to that hill.

249
00:17:31,134 --> 00:17:35,636
{\an1}Well, you can't. The Lord Elder
says that no one is allowed to
go near there.

250
00:17:35,669 --> 00:17:37,035
Oh... really?

251
00:17:37,068 --> 00:17:38,269
{\an1}Go on, leave.

252
00:17:38,302 --> 00:17:40,802
{\an1}C'mon, Ashura, let's go.

253
00:17:40,836 --> 00:17:42,470
{\an1}All right.

254
00:17:44,069 --> 00:17:45,704
{\an1}Something suspicious
is going on...

255
00:17:45,738 --> 00:17:49,738
{\an1}Yeah, maybe there is a
problem here, after all.

256
00:17:53,338 --> 00:17:57,373
{\an1}Oh! Hey, I know you!  You're
that beauty from yesterday!

257
00:17:57,406 --> 00:18:02,072
{\an4}What perfect timing! So,
listen, we're planning on
staying in this village for
a little while.

258
00:18:02,106 --> 00:18:04,507
{\an1}I'm hoping you can
show us around.

259
00:18:04,540 --> 00:18:07,073
{\an1}This is Ashura and I'm Tai-!

260
00:18:08,440 --> 00:18:12,308
{\an1}My name is Kanna. So,
are you a doctor or what?

261
00:18:12,341 --> 00:18:13,974
{\an1}Uh, no, not really...

262
00:18:14,008 --> 00:18:16,542
{\an1}He healed you because
he knows Ninshu.

263
00:18:16,576 --> 00:18:18,808
{\an1}Ninshu?  I see...

264
00:18:18,842 --> 00:18:22,010
{\an1}That's it... Can you
heal illnesses, too?

265
00:18:22,043 --> 00:18:23,943
Illnesses?

266
00:18:28,311 --> 00:18:30,044
{\an1}Come with me.

267
00:18:37,245 --> 00:18:38,911
What's this?

268
00:18:38,945 --> 00:18:40,912
A medical clinic.

269
00:18:40,946 --> 00:18:44,280
Please, I... I want you
to cure my mom's illness.

270
00:18:46,813 --> 00:18:52,415
Mother... She's been
unconscious for a long time.

271
00:18:56,848 --> 00:19:00,683
{\an8}<i>(Thinking)</i>
<i>What is this? I sense</i>
<i>a strong chakra...</i>

272
00:19:02,449 --> 00:19:04,783
{\an7}<i>Could this be from</i>
<i>the Divine Tree?</i>

273
00:19:11,718 --> 00:19:14,851
[grunt]

274
00:19:20,052 --> 00:19:25,153
{\an1}It's no good. I'm not able
to cure this sickness with
my power. I'm sorry.

275
00:19:25,186 --> 00:19:26,487
{\an1}I see... Are all these other
people like your mother?

276
00:19:26,520 --> 00:19:29,121
{\an1}Are all these other
people like your mother?

277
00:19:29,154 --> 00:19:30,987
{\an1}Yes.

278
00:19:33,987 --> 00:19:36,155
{\an1}Ashura... Come here...

279
00:19:39,955 --> 00:19:43,523
{\an1}<i>These are graves, aren't they?</i>

280
00:19:43,556 --> 00:19:46,657
{\an1}I guess it's no wonder that
this place felt so creepy...

281
00:19:46,690 --> 00:19:49,291
{\an1}And this illness caused
all of these deaths?

282
00:19:49,324 --> 00:19:52,424
That's right.

283
00:19:54,759 --> 00:19:56,991
{\an1}There's no choice, I have to go.

284
00:20:01,626 --> 00:20:03,825
[gasps]

285
00:20:03,859 --> 00:20:05,594
Hey!  You're--!

286
00:20:05,627 --> 00:20:07,627
{\an1}I'm sorry, but I'm gonna
need you go to sleep.

287
00:20:07,661 --> 00:20:11,027
{\an1}[concentrating grunts]

288
00:20:11,060 --> 00:20:12,495
Uh, what are you doing?

289
00:20:12,528 --> 00:20:15,361
{\an1}What were the Visual
Prowess signs again?

290
00:20:15,395 --> 00:20:18,029
{\an5}<i>[thuds]</i>
Huh?

291
00:20:18,062 --> 00:20:18,928
{\an1}This way is easier
and much faster.

292
00:20:23,764 --> 00:20:25,363
{\an1}[sheepish chuckle]

293
00:20:45,166 --> 00:20:46,400
{\an1}There's a cave here.

294
00:20:46,433 --> 00:20:47,600
{\an1}Let's check it out.

295
00:21:03,869 --> 00:21:06,270
{\an1}What is this place?

296
00:21:06,304 --> 00:21:08,704
{\an1}I didn't think it would
be like this inside!

297
00:21:08,737 --> 00:21:12,003
{\an1}I've heard legends about
the Divine Tree, but...

298
00:21:12,037 --> 00:21:15,004
{\an1}This is--?!

299
00:21:15,038 --> 00:21:21,773
{\an1}There's no doubt.
This is the Divine Tree.

